1
00:00:01,627 --> 00:00:04,129
Do you have what it
takes to Buddyfight?

2
00:00:04,129 --> 00:00:06,798
Choose your favorite world,
and use special cards

3
00:00:06,798 --> 00:00:10,260
to summon its powerful
monsters into reality.

4
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:11,428
Challenge other fighters,

5
00:00:11,428 --> 00:00:15,182
and Buddycall your toughest
ally to fight by your side.

6
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:18,185
Get ready to raise the flag.

7
00:00:18,185 --> 00:00:23,774
♪

8
00:00:23,774 --> 00:00:25,734
Ah!

9
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:29,988
How careless of you.

10
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,531
What a waste.

11
00:00:31,531 --> 00:00:34,743
So much for leaving
a lasting impression.

12
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:38,372
Now it's my turn to have fun.

13
00:00:38,372 --> 00:00:41,250
Glory Seeker will
finish you off.

14
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:43,877
If only I fought better.

15
00:00:43,877 --> 00:00:46,088
♪

16
00:00:46,088 --> 00:00:48,382
(exploding)

17
00:00:48,382 --> 00:02:16,136
♪

18
00:02:22,059 --> 00:02:25,771
(whooshing)

19
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:34,029
(whooshing)

20
00:02:37,616 --> 00:02:39,076
Good morning, Gao.

21
00:02:39,076 --> 00:02:40,535
S'up, guys?

22
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:41,662
Come on, tell us.

23
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:43,455
Have you heard
any news from Kiri?

24
00:02:43,455 --> 00:02:45,290
No, nothing yet.

25
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:48,335
Maybe he's super busy with
the move and everything.

26
00:02:48,335 --> 00:02:50,671
Yeah.

27
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:52,506
I am kind of worried though.

28
00:02:52,506 --> 00:02:55,300
It's been a month.

29
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,803
What's this on your desk?

30
00:02:57,803 --> 00:02:59,888
A letter.

31
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,098
Hmm?

32
00:03:01,098 --> 00:03:02,641
‐Oh, man!
‐Weird.

33
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:05,727
It's frozen to the desk.

34
00:03:05,727 --> 00:03:08,980
Uh, hmm.

35
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:11,483
Hey, guys, it's from Kiri!

36
00:03:11,483 --> 00:03:13,318
(gasping)

37
00:03:16,071 --> 00:03:18,156
(whirring)

38
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:19,616
(roaring)

39
00:03:23,161 --> 00:03:24,538
I can't remember
the last time

40
00:03:24,538 --> 00:03:26,164
I got snail mail
from someone.

41
00:03:26,164 --> 00:03:28,500
Kiri always was
kind of old school.

42
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:31,002
What I want to know is how
he froze it to your desk.

43
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:34,089
Okay, it says, "Dear Gao,

44
00:03:34,089 --> 00:03:35,257
Do you remember me?

45
00:03:35,257 --> 00:03:36,299
I'm Kiri.

46
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:38,301
I guess it hasn't
been that long.

47
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:40,220
Sorry that I left
without saying goodbye.

48
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,721
It all happened so fast.

49
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:44,516
My new school is called
Fumiya Daini Elementary,

50
00:03:44,516 --> 00:03:46,935
and Buddyfighting is
really popular here.

51
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:48,895
I've had lots of
time to practice,

52
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,439
and not to brag or anything,

53
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,816
but I think I've become
a much stronger player.

54
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:54,359
Anyway, it'd be really cool

55
00:03:54,359 --> 00:03:56,528
if you could come
up and visit me.

56
00:03:56,528 --> 00:03:57,696
I'd give anything to have

57
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:59,948
another Buddyfight
with you someday.

58
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,199
See ya soon.

59
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:02,659
Your good friend, Kiri."

60
00:04:04,161 --> 00:04:05,537
Pretty cool, right?

61
00:04:05,537 --> 00:04:07,706
Yeah, it sounds like
he's doing okay.

62
00:04:07,706 --> 00:04:09,875
He said he wants to
fight against me again.

63
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:11,501
That'd be so awesome!

64
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:15,422
Uh, that almost sounded
like a challenge.

65
00:04:15,422 --> 00:04:16,715
(laughing)

66
00:04:16,715 --> 00:04:18,049
I don't think so.

67
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,301
So how far away is

68
00:04:19,301 --> 00:04:21,428
his whatchamacallit
elementary school?

69
00:04:21,428 --> 00:04:22,804
I can tell you in one sec.

70
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:24,973
Yep, there it is, right here.

71
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:25,891
Ooh, handy.

72
00:04:25,891 --> 00:04:27,350
That's actually not too far.

73
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,436
Maybe we should go give
him a surprise visit.

74
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:32,647
We should take a picnic there
on the weekend or something.

75
00:04:32,647 --> 00:04:34,024
Weekend, why wait?

76
00:04:34,024 --> 00:04:35,901
Let's drop in on him today.

77
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:37,569
I'm gonna jet
right after school

78
00:04:37,569 --> 00:04:39,196
if you want to come along.

79
00:04:39,196 --> 00:04:40,322
(clock chiming)

80
00:04:40,322 --> 00:04:41,740
Buddy Skill on.

81
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:43,992
(whooshing)

82
00:04:45,243 --> 00:04:47,245
Sometimes I wish
I had a Buddy,

83
00:04:47,245 --> 00:04:48,747
then I'd have
a ride like that.

84
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:49,748
Don't worry, Baku.

85
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:51,875
You can ride the bus with me.

86
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:52,959
What ya lookin' at?

87
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:55,420
He forgot his bag.

88
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:58,089
Mm, that guy
forgets everything.

89
00:04:58,089 --> 00:05:00,133
(birds chirping)

90
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:04,763
You cheated.

91
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:06,890
Nah, you're just slow.

92
00:05:06,890 --> 00:05:08,850
What do you mean,
I'm not slow!

93
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:10,936
Like molasses on a cold day.

94
00:05:10,936 --> 00:05:12,771
(grunting)

95
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:13,939
So what now?

96
00:05:13,939 --> 00:05:16,817
We'll just ask around
till we find him.

97
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:18,902
‐Hey, guys!
‐Huh?

98
00:05:18,902 --> 00:05:19,820
How's it going?

99
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:21,822
Have you seen a guy
called Kiri anywhere?

100
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:24,157
You mean Kiri Hyoryu?

101
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:27,702
He's a friend of mine,
he used to go to my school.

102
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:28,745
Huh?

103
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:30,664
Uh...

104
00:05:30,664 --> 00:05:32,791
(whooshing)

105
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:34,251
(shouting)

106
00:05:34,251 --> 00:05:35,669
Guys, watch out!

107
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:40,340
(whimpering)

108
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:42,634
What's wrong?

109
00:05:42,634 --> 00:05:45,387
‐Hey, Gao.
‐Huh?

110
00:05:45,387 --> 00:05:47,305
♪

111
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:50,058
I guess this means
you got my letter.

112
00:05:50,058 --> 00:05:51,268
Wow, you're freezing!

113
00:05:51,268 --> 00:05:52,811
Follow me to
the playing field.

114
00:05:52,811 --> 00:05:55,272
I figured we could have
our Buddyfight there.

115
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:56,940
What's the rush?

116
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:57,983
Hey, wait up!

117
00:05:57,983 --> 00:05:58,984
(chuckles)

118
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:01,778
Sweet, looks like our
boy has finally arrived.

119
00:06:01,778 --> 00:06:03,488
Now it's time
for a little fun.

120
00:06:03,488 --> 00:06:05,782
Mikado's in for
a frosty treat.

121
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:07,158
Mmm.

122
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:10,120
♪

123
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,580
I'm ready to fight you.

124
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:15,000
I've been thinking about
it since I left Aibo.

125
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,002
Why is he holding
a Dark Core case?

126
00:06:17,002 --> 00:06:19,170
No way, where'd
you get that thing?

127
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:21,423
Instead of worrying
about my deck,

128
00:06:21,423 --> 00:06:23,133
you should focus
on the match.

129
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:25,051
Hey, what's gotten
into you, Kiri?

130
00:06:25,051 --> 00:06:27,012
You know how dangerous
that thing is,

131
00:06:27,012 --> 00:06:28,763
so what the heck are
you doing with it?

132
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,015
I know, relax.

133
00:06:30,015 --> 00:06:31,516
I can't resist this power.

134
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:32,809
It's too important to me.

135
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:34,227
Are you for real?

136
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:37,689
Like frozen water, my power
makes me tough to break.

137
00:06:37,689 --> 00:06:41,735
Dark Luminize,
Unstoppable Ice Blizzard!

138
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:44,070
Come on, what are
you waiting for?

139
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:46,531
Luminize.

140
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:48,533
I think I liked
the old Kiri better.

141
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:50,076
You could say that again.

142
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:53,330
Cracking the skies
and rumbling the ground,

143
00:06:53,330 --> 00:06:57,542
luminize the Forceful
Tempest Thunder Knights!

144
00:06:57,542 --> 00:07:01,546
Let me introduce you
to my Buddy monster.

145
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:02,714
Whoa‐ho‐ho!

146
00:07:02,714 --> 00:07:05,717
Is it me or is it
chilly in here?

147
00:07:05,717 --> 00:07:08,219
Woo, brr!

148
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,220
What's wrong?

149
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:11,056
Got a little brain freeze?

150
00:07:11,056 --> 00:07:12,724
Who is this guy?

151
00:07:12,724 --> 00:07:15,101
Sorry, but just so you know,

152
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:18,063
I'm gonna destroy that
Dark Core deck case.

153
00:07:18,063 --> 00:07:19,439
What did you just say?

154
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:23,526
Ha, I knew all along you're
just like everyone else.

155
00:07:23,526 --> 00:07:26,404
(gasping)

156
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:27,947
Yes, that's it, game over!

157
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,199
The winner is me!

158
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:32,160
‐Oh.
‐I'll be taking this.

159
00:07:32,160 --> 00:07:33,203
Ah.

160
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:36,289
Wow, Demon Wolf, Fenrir,
and it's a special rare!

161
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:38,333
Oh, man, I've always
wanted one of these!

162
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,501
Today's my lucky day.

163
00:07:39,501 --> 00:07:42,587
No way, I never agreed to
betting any of my cards!

164
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:43,922
Now, come on, give it back.

165
00:07:43,922 --> 00:07:48,093
Sorry, but the winner
gets to call the shots.

166
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:50,178
I'm no good at this game.

167
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:52,263
I'll never win my card back.

168
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:55,058
I don't get why
I'm not improving.

169
00:07:55,058 --> 00:07:57,268
♪

170
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:58,812
You could never understand

171
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,939
what it's been
like for me, Gao.

172
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:03,274
Well, then why don't
you tell me about it?

173
00:08:03,274 --> 00:08:04,776
Maybe some other time.

174
00:08:04,776 --> 00:08:06,111
Now let's get started.

175
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:07,112
Freeze!

176
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:09,781
Now it's time to
raise the flag!

177
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:12,367
I fight for Dragon World!

178
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:14,494
And I fight for Legend World.

179
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:16,746
So, you mind if I go first?

180
00:08:16,746 --> 00:08:17,789
Be my guest.

181
00:08:17,789 --> 00:08:20,792
Neither of us is gonna
stop until you chill out.

182
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:22,293
We'll just see about that.

183
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:25,046
'Kay, charge and draw.

184
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:28,550
Now, I'll equip
with Rune Staff.

185
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:31,136
♪

186
00:08:31,136 --> 00:08:35,348
I call to center Mighty
Frost Giant, Hrimthurs.

187
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:37,100
I destroy.

188
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,810
Go and attack the fighter!

189
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:42,480
Permafrost wave!

190
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,982
End of move.

191
00:08:43,982 --> 00:08:45,275
Your move.

192
00:08:45,275 --> 00:08:46,276
I don't get it.

193
00:08:46,276 --> 00:08:49,446
What happened to you, man?

194
00:08:49,446 --> 00:08:51,031
No answer, huh?

195
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:51,990
Then I draw.

196
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:53,408
Charge and draw.

197
00:08:53,408 --> 00:08:55,326
I buddy call to the right

198
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:58,329
Thunder Knights,
Drum Bunker Dragon!

199
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:00,415
That's me.

200
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:03,168
I call to the left
Iron‐Fist Dragon!

201
00:09:03,168 --> 00:09:04,836
Right cross to the chops.

202
00:09:04,836 --> 00:09:08,548
Watch this, now I equip
Thunderblade, Dragobreaker!

203
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,884
(grunting)

204
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:13,636
Set Spell, Thunder Formation!

205
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:16,681
The Thunder Knights Gao
Formation is complete.

206
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:19,350
Now it's time
to take the stage.

207
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:21,936
You should know my
tactics are foolproof.

208
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:22,854
It's a fact.

209
00:09:22,854 --> 00:09:25,482
My Dark Core provides
me with more power

210
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:27,984
than you could
possibly imagine.

211
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:29,235
(chuckles)

212
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:32,489
To think how far this
kid's come in only a month.

213
00:09:32,489 --> 00:09:34,866
♪

214
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:38,119
I heard Inaba took
one of your best cards.

215
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:39,162
Uh‐huh.

216
00:09:39,162 --> 00:09:40,622
How you doing, Kiri?

217
00:09:40,622 --> 00:09:42,457
Don't tell me you've
forgotten me already.

218
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:44,417
It's me, Davide Yamazaki.

219
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,336
There's just one
thing I gotta know.

220
00:09:46,336 --> 00:09:49,881
Do you really want to win it
back from Inaba or not, huh?

221
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:51,257
I could never beat him.

222
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:54,636
Even if I practiced every day,
I'm too weak a fighter.

223
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:56,387
You might be stronger
than you think.

224
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:59,057
Well, as long
as you have this.

225
00:09:59,057 --> 00:10:01,059
That's a Dark Core deck case.

226
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:03,686
Chillax, it's not
gonna bite you, kid.

227
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:05,063
Here, go on, take it.

228
00:10:05,063 --> 00:10:06,648
No way, not ever.

229
00:10:06,648 --> 00:10:07,982
Get away.

230
00:10:07,982 --> 00:10:09,234
(grunting)

231
00:10:09,234 --> 00:10:11,069
Whatever you might have heard,

232
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:12,987
I promise there's
no reason to fear it.

233
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:14,280
This will make you
the Buddyfighter

234
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,698
you've always wanted to be.

235
00:10:15,698 --> 00:10:17,325
You serious?

236
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:19,244
It really will?

237
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:20,787
I wouldn't lie to you, kid.

238
00:10:20,787 --> 00:10:21,913
As long as you have this,

239
00:10:21,913 --> 00:10:23,915
you'll be stronger
than anybody.

240
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:27,377
Then you can quit being so
shy and nervous all the time.

241
00:10:27,377 --> 00:10:29,754
Ah.

242
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:32,090
Okay, I‐‐I'll take it.

243
00:10:32,090 --> 00:10:34,509
I want to be the best ever.

244
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:39,347
(grunting)

245
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:41,057
(chuckles)

246
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:44,018
(gasping)

247
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:47,272
I told Kyoya I'd get him
to accept the dark power,

248
00:10:47,272 --> 00:10:48,523
and I delivered.

249
00:10:48,523 --> 00:10:51,276
There's no way he's
going to give all that up

250
00:10:51,276 --> 00:10:52,944
now that he's had a taste.

251
00:10:52,944 --> 00:10:54,445
Mm.

252
00:10:59,826 --> 00:11:02,245
Okay, Drum, go
take out Hrimthurs.

253
00:11:02,245 --> 00:11:03,621
Yeah!

254
00:11:03,621 --> 00:11:05,165
Even protecting your center

255
00:11:05,165 --> 00:11:08,376
won't help you defend
against my punishing attack!

256
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:09,878
(grunting)

257
00:11:09,878 --> 00:11:11,337
Penetrate!

258
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:13,089
‐Hm.
‐Ha!

259
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:16,259
(grunting)

260
00:11:16,259 --> 00:11:17,510
You're up, Iron‐Fist.

261
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:19,220
Show him what you're made of.

262
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:21,222
(grunting)

263
00:11:21,222 --> 00:11:23,308
Time to mix it up.

264
00:11:23,308 --> 00:11:27,937
Then I cast the
Shield of Achilles.

265
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:29,355
Surprise!

266
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:31,566
(grunting)

267
00:11:31,566 --> 00:11:33,735
♪

268
00:11:33,735 --> 00:11:34,986
End of move.

269
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:37,822
Brr, that was a
frosty formation

270
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:39,032
you just tossed out there.

271
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:41,201
Quick question,
cold enough for ya?

272
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:44,579
Ah, he's starting to
make my scales crawl.

273
00:11:44,579 --> 00:11:45,705
Your move.

274
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:47,040
Thanks, that was great.

275
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:50,168
I've always been curious about
your Gao Formation attack.

276
00:11:50,168 --> 00:11:53,463
Rather impressive,
but it doesn't matter

277
00:11:53,463 --> 00:11:56,132
'cause I'm gonna win this.

278
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:58,092
♪

279
00:11:58,092 --> 00:12:01,179
I cast Symbel Gard!

280
00:12:01,179 --> 00:12:03,556
And I draw two cards
from the deck.

281
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:06,976
Releasing Set Spell,
Great Spell Fimbulwinter.

282
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:09,729
♪

283
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:12,273
I don't think I've come
across that one before.

284
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:14,609
Over the next turns,
I can discard the two cards

285
00:12:14,609 --> 00:12:17,028
that I just got, and when
those are down to zero,

286
00:12:17,028 --> 00:12:18,571
I get to draw another card.

287
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:19,864
You following, Gao?

288
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:21,199
You bet I am.

289
00:12:21,199 --> 00:12:22,367
Watch and see.

290
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:24,369
I call Corpse
Swallower Hraesvelgr

291
00:12:24,369 --> 00:12:26,537
to the right position
and soul sheltering

292
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:29,290
Fog Wall, Nevel Vans
to the center.

293
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:32,293
♪

294
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:33,711
What the...

295
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:36,714
Cool thing about Nevel Vans
is if there's another monster

296
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:40,009
in the field, he can
never be destroyed.

297
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:41,719
Time to move to
the center, Drum,

298
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:43,805
and Iron‐Fist
over to the right.

299
00:12:43,805 --> 00:12:45,556
Yeah!

300
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:47,558
♪

301
00:12:47,558 --> 00:12:49,310
The effect of the
Thunder Formation

302
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:51,688
adds two to my gauge.

303
00:12:51,688 --> 00:12:54,732
You're on the losing
side of this match.

304
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:56,985
Now, Hraesvelgr
attacks Iron‐Fist.

305
00:12:56,985 --> 00:12:59,654
♪

306
00:12:59,654 --> 00:13:02,907
(grunting)

307
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:03,866
Ah!

308
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:05,285
End of move.

309
00:13:05,285 --> 00:13:08,371
The attack and critical for
Nevel Vans are just a zero.

310
00:13:08,371 --> 00:13:11,582
You see, Gao, I told
you it wasn't much.

311
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:12,792
Come on, Kiri.

312
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:15,420
I just know you're in there.

313
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:18,506
Hey, Davide?

314
00:13:18,506 --> 00:13:19,757
Oh, hi, Inaba.

315
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:21,259
You guys should
be watching this.

316
00:13:21,259 --> 00:13:22,343
It's a pretty awesome match.

317
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:24,345
About that,
we've been talking,

318
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:26,264
and for the record,
we don't want anything

319
00:13:26,264 --> 00:13:27,932
to do with Kiri anymore.

320
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:28,891
Game over.

321
00:13:28,891 --> 00:13:31,060
Winner, Kiri Hyoryu.

322
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:32,937
Somebody got frozen.

323
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,272
Ah!

324
00:13:34,272 --> 00:13:37,317
(groaning)

325
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:40,570
♪

326
00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:43,114
(whimpering)

327
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:45,241
♪

328
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:46,993
Looks like I win again.

329
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,746
Oh, I'm sure you'll
win one of these days.

330
00:13:49,746 --> 00:13:51,956
Need a little help getting
out of those snow shoes?

331
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:53,624
Ahh!

332
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:55,209
I'll take that card.

333
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,128
It's mine, after all.

334
00:13:57,128 --> 00:13:59,464
The guy's just gotten
a little too hardcore.

335
00:13:59,464 --> 00:14:01,215
You don't know anything.

336
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:02,550
Kiri's on his way to becoming

337
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:04,802
one of the best
Buddyfighters there ever was,

338
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:07,305
even better than
Mikado there.

339
00:14:07,305 --> 00:14:09,974
You'll see soon enough.

340
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:11,559
(neighing)

341
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:13,561
I will ride again!

342
00:14:13,561 --> 00:14:15,229
End of move.

343
00:14:15,229 --> 00:14:17,190
We're dropping like flies.

344
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:19,150
Your move.

345
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:20,443
Draw!

346
00:14:20,443 --> 00:14:21,736
Charge and draw!

347
00:14:21,736 --> 00:14:23,154
All right.

348
00:14:23,154 --> 00:14:24,697
He's playing defense,

349
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:28,618
destroying my monsters one at
a time, all casual and stuff.

350
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:32,163
What's his deal?

351
00:14:32,163 --> 00:14:34,499
I gotta get to
the bottom of this.

352
00:14:34,499 --> 00:14:36,250
Ya think?

353
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:38,628
I always find a way
to beat my opponents

354
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:40,755
by figuring out
their strategy.

355
00:14:40,755 --> 00:14:44,092
And here I thought it was
just dumb luck all this time.

356
00:14:44,092 --> 00:14:45,218
I'm stumped.

357
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:47,720
I have no idea what Kiri's
up to or even thinking.

358
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,430
Then take it from me, kid.

359
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:51,682
There's only one
thing for us to do.

360
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,434
And what's that?

361
00:14:53,434 --> 00:14:55,645
We gotta hit him with
an all‐out attack,

362
00:14:55,645 --> 00:14:57,688
everything we've
got, ya feel me?

363
00:14:57,688 --> 00:15:00,691
Do you want to destroy
that Dark Core or not?

364
00:15:00,691 --> 00:15:02,068
Ah.

365
00:15:02,068 --> 00:15:03,528
Earth to kid.

366
00:15:03,528 --> 00:15:04,779
I hear you, Drum.

367
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:06,906
I know what I gotta do.

368
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:10,201
I'm gonna call Iron‐Fist
Dragon to the left position.

369
00:15:10,201 --> 00:15:11,744
(grunting)

370
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:13,538
Then, Drum, shift
over to the right

371
00:15:13,538 --> 00:15:15,206
and destroy that Sleipnir.

372
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:17,333
Ya caught me on a good day.

373
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:20,002
Crash, Drill Ram Bunker!

374
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:22,130
(neighing)

375
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:25,049
Yippee‐kay‐ay, that's
how we do it downtown.

376
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:27,135
'Kay, let's make
this count, Iron‐Fist.

377
00:15:27,135 --> 00:15:28,719
Attack Nevel Van!

378
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:32,181
(grunting)

379
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:34,559
♪

380
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:35,726
Heads up!

381
00:15:35,726 --> 00:15:37,103
Hi‐ya!

382
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:40,148
I cast Power of Mythology.

383
00:15:40,148 --> 00:15:42,441
(grunting)

384
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:44,402
I may have lost
my Nevel Vans,

385
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:46,571
but I kept my damage at zero.

386
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:49,407
Come on, Gao, this is
the moment of truth.

387
00:15:49,407 --> 00:15:50,241
I hear ya.

388
00:15:50,241 --> 00:15:52,118
Okay, time for final phase.

389
00:15:52,118 --> 00:15:52,952
You ready for it?

390
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,413
I cast the mighty
Thunder Formation.

391
00:15:55,413 --> 00:15:57,373
When it's activated,
the three top cards

392
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:00,543
of the deck are turned over.

393
00:16:00,543 --> 00:16:02,712
And if any of them happen
to be Thunder Knights,

394
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:06,132
then I can call as many
monsters as I want.

395
00:16:06,132 --> 00:16:08,551
♪

396
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:09,594
Let's rock this.

397
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:12,513
I call Broadsword Dragon
to the right and the left.

398
00:16:12,513 --> 00:16:14,432
Attack the fighter!

399
00:16:14,432 --> 00:16:17,393
My sword strikes through
the air like lightning.

400
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:19,437
The Broadsword Dragon
Thunder Knights

401
00:16:19,437 --> 00:16:21,314
will conquer the enemy!

402
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:23,107
Thunderclap!

403
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:24,734
(grunting)

404
00:16:24,734 --> 00:16:26,360
End of move.

405
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,029
So tell me, who gave you

406
00:16:28,029 --> 00:16:30,448
that dangerous
Dark Core case anyway?

407
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:31,949
So many questions.

408
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:33,159
It's none of your business.

409
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:34,619
We only have one
life point left.

410
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:36,704
It's starting to
freeze over, you know.

411
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:40,374
I was just warming up, Joker.

412
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:42,460
But now I'm going to end it.

413
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:43,628
How do you figure?

414
00:16:43,628 --> 00:16:44,629
Your move.

415
00:16:44,629 --> 00:16:46,297
I draw.

416
00:16:46,297 --> 00:16:48,925
Charge and draw.

417
00:16:48,925 --> 00:16:50,426
Now, once three
turns have past,

418
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:52,470
after setting Great
Spell, Fimbulwinter

419
00:16:52,470 --> 00:16:55,765
and the soul's at zero,
I'm able to draw one card.

420
00:16:55,765 --> 00:16:58,392
Now I'm going to use
Set Spell Rain Gleipnir

421
00:16:58,392 --> 00:17:00,811
and move my super‐strong
size three monster

422
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,230
from the drop zone
to the soul.

423
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:04,273
Demon Wolf, Fenrir.

424
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:07,151
That's right, the same
monster you chose for me

425
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,152
when I was at Aibo.

426
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:09,320
Rather fitting, huh?

427
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:11,155
Isn't it weird to
think you had a hand

428
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:12,782
in causing your own defeat?

429
00:17:12,782 --> 00:17:14,659
♪

430
00:17:14,659 --> 00:17:16,869
I don't really see
what your point is.

431
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:17,828
Just watch.

432
00:17:17,828 --> 00:17:20,831
Cast Great Spell, Ragnarok.

433
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:22,375
Uh...

434
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:24,543
When the great
Fimbulwinter continues

435
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,087
its storm for three years,

436
00:17:26,087 --> 00:17:28,506
it is said that the world
will come to an end.

437
00:17:28,506 --> 00:17:30,341
(grunting)

438
00:17:30,341 --> 00:17:32,051
And Ragnarok will rain,

439
00:17:32,051 --> 00:17:34,095
a great spell that
can only be activated

440
00:17:34,095 --> 00:17:36,013
when there's a
Fimbulwinter in the field

441
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:37,473
and the soul is at zero.

442
00:17:37,473 --> 00:17:39,517
With its effect,
all cards on the field

443
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:42,353
and in the player's hands
are destroyed and discarded.

444
00:17:42,353 --> 00:17:44,355
(crunching)

445
00:17:44,355 --> 00:17:47,149
(shattering)

446
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,068
♪

447
00:17:49,068 --> 00:17:50,945
Nothing like putting
things on ice.

448
00:17:50,945 --> 00:17:53,531
Brr, did somebody
turn up the AC?

449
00:17:53,531 --> 00:17:56,576
Of course, nothing is immune
to its devastating power,

450
00:17:56,576 --> 00:17:58,911
equipped items and
Soulguards included.

451
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:02,081
Even my own Gleipnir
gets destroyed.

452
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:03,874
And when a
Gleipnir's destroyed,

453
00:18:03,874 --> 00:18:05,668
the monsters
entered into the soul

454
00:18:05,668 --> 00:18:07,920
can be called at no cost.

455
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:11,173
♪

456
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:12,341
(roaring)

457
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:14,635
Where is my first prey?

458
00:18:14,635 --> 00:18:16,470
I can also call this monster

459
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:18,097
that's been discarded
from the hand.

460
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:21,559
I buddy call Ice Blade,
Joker to the right position.

461
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:23,352
Ice, ice, baby!

462
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:26,022
When I'm called,
everything freezes.

463
00:18:26,022 --> 00:18:28,190
Fenrir's long‐range
attack is pointless

464
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,901
when restricted by so
many spells and monsters,

465
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:33,779
so I thought to myself,
"Why not just destroy it all?"

466
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:36,240
The field, hands, everything.

467
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:38,743
Has everything you've
worked for all been for this,

468
00:18:38,743 --> 00:18:41,120
to wipe out everything
and call back a monster

469
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,747
to a world where
nothing remains?

470
00:18:42,747 --> 00:18:44,749
I gotta say,
I'm pretty surprised, man.

471
00:18:44,749 --> 00:18:46,876
‐This isn't you.
‐Congratulations, Gao.

472
00:18:46,876 --> 00:18:48,044
You pieced it together.

473
00:18:48,044 --> 00:18:50,755
I finally completed my
ultimate combo deck.

474
00:18:50,755 --> 00:18:52,381
And it's here.

475
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:54,175
Gleipnir slice.

476
00:18:54,175 --> 00:18:56,761
(grunting)

477
00:18:56,761 --> 00:18:58,304
My turn!

478
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:00,431
Howling moon blast!

479
00:19:00,431 --> 00:19:03,017
♪

480
00:19:03,017 --> 00:19:04,685
End of move.

481
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:06,437
(laughing)

482
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,606
He wiped out all the
spells and monsters

483
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:11,108
and took away Mikado's
ability to defend.

484
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:12,860
‐I like it.
‐Huh?

485
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:13,986
Hold on, check it out.

486
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:15,946
Someone's coming.

487
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:19,033
Hmm, I wondered when
they'd get here.

488
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:23,496
This is it, Gao.

489
00:19:23,496 --> 00:19:25,373
You have no more
cards in your hand

490
00:19:25,373 --> 00:19:26,624
and no more monsters,

491
00:19:26,624 --> 00:19:29,752
and I have mighty
Fenrir in my center.

492
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:31,712
Guess you're not as good
as everyone thinks you are.

493
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:35,424
Ooh, don't look now, but
someone's almost out cold.

494
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:36,884
I gotta hand it to ya.

495
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:40,429
You've put together
an awesome combo here.

496
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:46,477
But I'm confused why you need
to depend on that dark power.

497
00:19:46,477 --> 00:19:48,521
To win, why else?

498
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:51,816
Is winning really
that important?

499
00:19:51,816 --> 00:19:52,817
Of course it is.

500
00:19:52,817 --> 00:19:53,984
Winning is everything.

501
00:19:53,984 --> 00:19:56,320
Nothing else
matters to me at all.

502
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:58,572
(grunting)

503
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:03,536
You can't actually
believe that.

504
00:20:03,536 --> 00:20:05,121
I call to the center

505
00:20:05,121 --> 00:20:08,040
the Thunder Knight,
Bastard‐sword Dragon.

506
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:10,042
Did he say the
Bastard‐sword Dragon?

507
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:11,168
What's the matter, Kiri?

508
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:13,170
You're breaking
into a cold sweat.

509
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:14,505
What's your problem?

510
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:15,548
Come on!

511
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:16,757
You really want to know?

512
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:18,342
I got tired of losing

513
00:20:18,342 --> 00:20:20,553
and tired of feeling
cheated all the time.

514
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:22,847
But you wouldn't know
about that, would you?

515
00:20:22,847 --> 00:20:26,016
The Dark Core will make
you throw everything away!

516
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:28,102
(shouting)

517
00:20:28,102 --> 00:20:30,646
♪

518
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,398
There are some
things more important

519
00:20:32,398 --> 00:20:33,399
than winning and losing.

520
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:35,067
You should know that!

521
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:37,278
This will teach you
right from wrong!

522
00:20:37,278 --> 00:20:40,030
(grunting)

523
00:20:41,574 --> 00:20:42,616
Game over.

524
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:45,453
Winner, Gao Mikado.

525
00:20:45,453 --> 00:20:49,582
Thanks, but this doesn't
really feel like winning.

526
00:20:49,582 --> 00:20:50,666
Nice finish!

527
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:53,043
Hey, glad to see you
guys finally made it.

528
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:56,172
Not all of us have
a buddy skill, bro.

529
00:20:56,172 --> 00:20:59,216
Kiri, you okay?

530
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:01,969
Every match has to do
with timing and luck.

531
00:21:01,969 --> 00:21:03,554
The main thing
is to shake hands

532
00:21:03,554 --> 00:21:05,556
and be friends no
matter who wins.

533
00:21:05,556 --> 00:21:06,557
Now why don't you give me

534
00:21:06,557 --> 00:21:08,225
that crazy Dark
Core deck case?

535
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:10,936
I mean, you just proved that
you don't need it, right?

536
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:12,605
Uh, no way!

537
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:14,273
But I‐‐

538
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:17,902
Losing to you means I do
need this thing, and badly.

539
00:21:17,902 --> 00:21:20,613
See, everyone wants
to take it from you,

540
00:21:20,613 --> 00:21:23,073
just like I told you.

541
00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:24,700
Who are you?

542
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,243
Davide Yamazaki.

543
00:21:26,243 --> 00:21:29,455
You could say I'm Kiri's
one and only true friend.

544
00:21:29,455 --> 00:21:31,415
So you brainwashed him.

545
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:33,083
Ha, he was right about you.

546
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:34,043
You're really intense.

547
00:21:34,043 --> 00:21:36,045
Listen, this isn't
Aibo, all right?

548
00:21:36,045 --> 00:21:37,171
Here, we don't just go around

549
00:21:37,171 --> 00:21:39,548
trying to steal
people's stuff.

550
00:21:39,548 --> 00:21:41,759
Remember, no one gets
to boss you around.

551
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:44,553
They can try all they want to
convince you to hand it over,

552
00:21:44,553 --> 00:21:46,263
but you're free to
make up your own mind.

553
00:21:46,263 --> 00:21:47,389
Do you hear what I'm saying?

554
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:49,934
Don't let them turn you
into a weakling again.

555
00:21:49,934 --> 00:21:51,477
That's not true!

556
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:52,311
Oh, really?

557
00:21:52,311 --> 00:21:53,771
So what do you
think's gonna happen

558
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:55,272
when he gives up his deck?

559
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:56,273
Come on, Kiri!

560
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:59,652
Listen to me, this guy
is not really your friend!

561
00:21:59,652 --> 00:22:00,903
(sighing)

562
00:22:00,903 --> 00:22:02,780
Please, give me the Dark Core

563
00:22:02,780 --> 00:22:05,616
and you'll see
that I'm right!

564
00:22:05,616 --> 00:22:07,201
(laughing)

565
00:22:07,201 --> 00:22:08,118
Nice try.

566
00:22:08,118 --> 00:22:10,371
‐Kiri!
‐Just go away!

567
00:22:10,371 --> 00:22:12,623
Hmm, some Fimbulwinter?

568
00:22:12,623 --> 00:22:13,749
The dark power!

569
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:15,543
Oh, man, this doesn't
look too good.

570
00:22:15,543 --> 00:22:16,627
I can't move my feet.

571
00:22:16,627 --> 00:22:19,505
Just for a second you can
see how I used to feel.

572
00:22:19,505 --> 00:22:20,673
Give me a chance!

573
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:22,883
It's us who were
never really friends.

574
00:22:22,883 --> 00:22:24,677
Don't go with him!

575
00:22:24,677 --> 00:22:28,597
I will never go back to being
that weakling ever again.

576
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:30,933
♪

577
00:22:30,933 --> 00:22:33,519
Come back!

578
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:35,896
♪

579
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:37,314
(grunting)

580
00:22:37,314 --> 00:22:39,275
Why can't I make him see?

581
00:22:39,275 --> 00:22:42,027
I'd rather lose a
match than a friend.

582
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:44,071
Why did he go away?

583
00:22:44,071 --> 00:22:46,991
It's not your fault.

584
00:22:49,285 --> 00:22:50,286
It's time for...

585
00:22:50,286 --> 00:22:51,579
...Tasuku and Gao's...

586
00:22:51,579 --> 00:22:53,789
...Card of the Day!

587
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:56,125
The Demon Wolf Fenrir
combo from last time

588
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:58,460
would be even more
powerful with Ragnarok.

589
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:00,004
Used with the
awesome Set Spell

590
00:23:00,004 --> 00:23:01,672
called Great Spell,
Fimbulwinter,

591
00:23:01,672 --> 00:23:04,341
which gets cast three
turns after it's been set,

592
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:06,468
Ragnarok wipes out
all cards on the field

593
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:07,845
and in both fighters' hands.

594
00:23:07,845 --> 00:23:10,931
So, then, if a Gleipnir was
in the field at the time...

595
00:23:10,931 --> 00:23:13,601
...only Fenrir can
enter the field.

596
00:23:13,601 --> 00:23:14,852
So what do you think, guys?

597
00:23:14,852 --> 00:23:16,395
Think you can open
up one of these?

598
00:23:16,395 --> 00:23:19,356
You'll never know
until you try.

599
00:23:19,356 --> 00:24:46,360
♪

600
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:52,783
Next time, two people come
forward with awesome decks

601
00:24:52,783 --> 00:24:54,368
that we thought
were just a myth.

602
00:24:54,368 --> 00:24:56,370
One of them is Magoroku Shido

603
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:58,455
and the other is
Davide Yamazaki.

604
00:24:58,455 --> 00:25:01,417
Next episode,
"The Terrifying Dragon World."

605
